<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
As things stand for sorcery, our relative utility in RvR is low.<P>I think the following three areas are needing improvements to make sorcery viable in RvR: 1)  Instant casts,  2) bolt range, and  3) sleep spells. <P>1) We need an instant cast stun or mesmerization spell or an ability allowing instant casts. Either that, or instant cast sleep spells need to be removed from RvR. <P>2) We need a bolt range spell that does more than simply interrupt.<P>3) Mesmerization needs to be changed for RvR. Most players hate being mesmerized for long periods of time, long sleep durations are simply too disempowering. On the other hand, the fact that we have no way of telling if the target has the one minute sleep spell invulnerability is unacceptable. Mesmerizations' utility in RvR is very low in most situations due to the many ways it can be broken, often inadvertantly. The current one minute sleep spell invulnerabiliy should be removed and replaced by a better system for RvR. Perhaps a solution could be to reduce all sleep spell durations by 1/2 for RvR and make diminishing returns work properly. Diminishing returns meaning that each subsequent sleep spell cast on a target lasts 1/2 of it's normal duration (next one cast before a timer expires would last 1/4 duration, then 1/8 duration, etc...) and is globally applied to all sleep spells. The diminishing returns timer could last for one minute after the last sleep spell ends. <P><BR>I did not include debuffs as needing improvements due to Sanya's recent comments regarding Champions' debuffs.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
