Actually, I'm not disregarding the usefulness of interrupts at bolt range. I do agree that amnesia does have more general utility in RvR than mezz. However, that is more of a reflection on the current uselessness of mezz than the usefulness of amnesia.<P>What I'm saying is that sorcerys' relative RvR usefulness is very low, including our bolt range ability. An amnesia spell that actually does something other than <I>tickle</I> would increase our usefulness.<P>On the other hand, maybe they should just change the spell effect to a hand that tickles your opponent's tummy with the sound of a baby laughing, I'd cast that just for grins.    <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> Troll says: "oh look the silly sorcerers at it again, time for him to take a (dirt) nap, muahaha".<P>Also, have fun interrupting all those instant casters out there. Not to mention archers with quick draw times, slower than amnesia but they usually get the jump on the interrupt game, which is all important.
